rooms.Name: The Mists Of Shannara
rooms.Description:
These dark mists have encompassed the land since the passing of Allanon the
third Great Druid.  Only the best elven trackers have seemed to find their
way through the mists to the halls of Paranor. You seem to hear a haunting
whisper in the breeze of the souls long past perhaps even Hadeshorn has given
up the dead to assist in this battlefield against Brona The Skull King.

rooms.Name: Gates of Paranor
rooms.Description:
The mists slowly dissipate here coalescing around a great oak door that seems
to stand without any means of support.  The forboding door glows with glyphs
of warding that drive you and the mists back away from it, and as if that
weren't enough protection for the Druids keep the master warrior Caerid Lock
himself is on guard here.

ExtraDescs.Description:
These Glyphs that ward the door are surrounded by a greyish-gold aura that
repels anything and anyone that comes near to it without wearing the seal of
the Druids.

rooms.Name: Main Entrance of the Grand halls of Paranor
rooms.Description:
This entrance shows Paranor to be more than a myth or a warded door as it had
previously seemed.  For the walls and floors are covered with mosaics that
seem to magically move about as they describe the history of Shannara and you
feel as if you were transported to a different time and place as you step
into this grand hall.

ExtraDescs.Description:

repels anything and anyone that comes near to it without wearing the seal of
the Druids.

rooms.Name: The Grand Hall of Paranor
rooms.Description:
This enormous hallway streches for what seems to hundreds of yards to ,from
at this distance, what appears to be a tiny oaken door with the same strange
glow as the main gate. You begin to sense that whatever secrets the keep may
hold are found past that door.  And you have a compelling urge to either find
out or die trying.

rooms.Name: End of the Great Hallway
rooms.Description:
It wasn't as long as you thought perhaps it was magickally enhanced to seem
like a huge distance to already weary travelers who have by either luck or
happenstance made it this far. The door ahead of you is warded even more so
than the gates to this great place and must hold the secret you are searching
for.

rooms.Name: Paranor's East wing Guard Barracks
rooms.Description:
This HUGE room is stacked top to bottom and bottom to top with bunk beds,
gear, lockers, and a huge repotoir of weapons that the hundreds of guards of
Paranor use to defend the keep.

rooms.Name: Paranor's West wing guard barracks
rooms.Description:
This HUGE room is stacked top to bottom and bottom to top with bunk beds,
gear, lockers, and a huge repotoir of weapons that the hundreds of guards of
Paranor use to defend the keep.

rooms.Name: The East Library of Paranor
rooms.Description:
This room is vastly huge stacked floor to ceiling with rows and rows of books
that the druids have collected over past two-thousand years.  All books of
science and magick ever known to exist since the time of faerie have at least
one worn beaten copy here, but they seem to hold together as if by some
unseen hand.

rooms.Name: The West Library of Paranor
rooms.Description:
This room is vastly huge stacked floor to ceiling with rows and rows of books
that the druids have collected over past two-thousand years.  All books of
science and magick ever known to exist since the time of faerie have at least
one worn beaten copy here, but they seem to hold together as if by some
unseen hand.

rooms.Name: The West Vault of Paranor
rooms.Description:
This immense vault is home to many of the artifacts of the old science that
destroyed this world over a thousand years ago. Kept here by the druids in
order that no-one might gain access to them and use them for destruction
again they are magickally warded off behind the massive vault doors.

rooms.Name: The West Vault of Paranor
rooms.Description:
This immense vault is home to many of the artifacts of the old science that
destroyed this world over a thousand years ago. Kept here by the druids in
order that no-one might gain access to them and use them for destruction
again they are magickally warded off behind the massive vault doors.

rooms.Name: The High Druid's Chamber
rooms.Description:
This is the Chamber of Athabasca the High Druid and keeper of the true Elit
Druin, the macikal symbol of the office of High Druid. It is said that the
Elit Druin gives all of Shannara it's power of protection and is embedded
with the very essence of the last faerie known to exist.

rooms.Name: The entrance to the HadeShorn
rooms.Description:
This is the most dreary place you have ever encountered and it seems that the
mists that are surrounding you come from a lake not too far to your north as
if the very soul of the land has come to a thin lifeline of smoke extending
from this black lake.

rooms.Name: Further into the HadeShorn pass
rooms.Description:
You stumble and fall over razor sharp rocks and crags as you attempt to cross
this god-forsaken wasteland towards the great HadeShorn. You begin to thank
the gods that Bremen had the sense to warn you to fly or else the journey
would have been even more difficult as you plummeted to your doom
one-thousand feet below you to the east or west.

rooms.Name: The HadeShorn Lake(outer rim)
rooms.Description:
You have come up against the very mouth of the HadeShorn which rests in the
great bowl of an long dead volcano.  The center of the lake boils and bubbles
as if the volcano is yet active, and as each bubble pops you can swear you
hear screams eminating from the gas that follows the sudden bursts.

rooms.Name: The Center of the HadeShorn
rooms.Description:
You seem to be floating on the breathes of mist that eminate from this great
lake as you float inches above it's poisoness surface. The screams of the
dead and damned are so loud that you can't make out anything else and the
voices are maddening.

rooms.Name: The Mists Of Shannara
rooms.Description:
These dark mists have encompassed the land since the passing of Allanon the
third Great Druid.  Only the best elven trackers have seemed to find their
way through the mists to the halls of Paranor. You seem to hear a haunting
whisper in the breeze of the souls long past perhaps even Hadeshorn has given
up the dead to assist in this battlefield against Brona The Skull King.
